WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:03.578
Lopez: Control 7-Adam-07.

00:03.580 --> 00:05.289
Show us at a vehicle stop
on Olympic and Avon.

00:05.290 --> 00:07.620
You got this.

00:11.420 --> 00:13.459
Sir, driver's license
and registration, please.

00:13.460 --> 00:14.789
Man:
What's the problem?

00:14.790 --> 00:16.459
You were doing 50
in a school zone.

00:16.460 --> 00:17.829
What's that sound?

00:17.830 --> 00:18.830
My bees.

00:18.831 --> 00:20.079
Your what?

00:20.080 --> 00:22.039
Bees.
I'm a beekeeper.

00:22.040 --> 00:24.039
But I don't know
if I'll be able to control them

00:24.040 --> 00:25.329
if you give me a ticket.

00:25.330 --> 00:27.039
Sir, threatening an officer
is a crime.

00:27.040 --> 00:28.540
Alright, step out of the car.

00:37.710 --> 00:39.419
You okay?

00:39.420 --> 00:40.789
Yeah. You?

00:40.790 --> 00:42.709
I sure am missing
my long sleeves.

00:42.710 --> 00:45.169
Do we go after him?

00:45.170 --> 00:48.789
Uh, all units, be on the lookout
for a blue minivan.

00:48.790 --> 00:50.289
Look out, it's...

00:50.290 --> 00:51.619
full of bees!

00:51.620 --> 00:54.999
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
whoa, oh, oh ♪

00:55.000 --> 00:57.160
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

01:02.830 --> 01:04.039
♪ Unh ♪

01:04.040 --> 01:08.669
♪♪

01:08.670 --> 01:09.789
♪ There it is ♪

01:09.790 --> 01:11.500
Well, hello!

01:12.500 --> 01:14.459
Well, hello to you, too.

01:14.460 --> 01:15.959
Mm. I was talking
to the coffee.

01:15.960 --> 01:17.209
Mm.

01:17.210 --> 01:19.289
It's too early for dad jokes.

01:19.290 --> 01:22.039
I woke up this morning
with an amazing idea...

01:22.040 --> 01:23.379
Hmm?

01:23.380 --> 01:26.419
For the layout
of the master closet.

01:26.420 --> 01:28.830
Tell me what you think.

01:30.380 --> 01:31.250
Mm.

01:31.251 --> 01:32.459
What?

01:32.460 --> 01:33.919
Nothing.

01:33.920 --> 01:37.499
I-I mean, I was...
I was married for 20 years.

01:37.500 --> 01:39.039
"Nothing" usually means
a whole lot of something.

01:39.040 --> 01:40.709
Well, I mean...

01:40.710 --> 01:44.079
you don't even have, like,
a-a built-in shoe rack.

01:44.080 --> 01:47.169
Oh, well, I got, what,
two pairs of shoes?

01:47.170 --> 01:48.919
Yeah, but I have a lot more.

01:48.920 --> 01:52.209
♪♪

01:52.210 --> 01:53.879
O-Oh. Yeah.
Uh, right.

01:53.880 --> 01:55.289
Uh, I-I mean, obviously, yeah.

01:55.290 --> 01:57.249
I mean, we haven't
even talked about the...

01:57.250 --> 01:58.619
Relax!

01:58.620 --> 02:01.669
It's fine. It's good.
I'm... I'm... I'm kidding.

02:01.670 --> 02:03.459
Right.
Yeah.

02:03.460 --> 02:05.749
I'm gonna, um...
I'm gonna get dressed.

02:05.750 --> 02:06.750
Okay.
Okay.

02:06.750 --> 02:07.540
Okay.
Yeah.

02:07.541 --> 02:12.539
♪♪

02:12.540 --> 02:19.079
♪♪

02:19.080 --> 02:20.709
I'm gonna lose it.

02:20.710 --> 02:22.579
Ah, you're back...

02:22.580 --> 02:23.789
You forget something?

02:23.790 --> 02:25.709
My car won't start.
Again.

02:25.710 --> 02:26.829
You need a new one.

02:26.830 --> 02:28.110
I need a healthier bank account.

02:29.500 --> 02:30.959
Uh, I can get you to work,

02:30.960 --> 02:32.459
but you're on your own
to get home.

02:32.460 --> 02:33.709
Why? What are you
doing tonight?

02:33.710 --> 02:34.959
Nothing.

02:34.960 --> 02:36.789
I mean, t-that thing.
I told you.

02:36.790 --> 02:37.919
What thing?

02:37.920 --> 02:40.000
At my mother's.
Remember?

02:41.290 --> 02:42.500
The mother I haven't met yet?

02:43.710 --> 02:46.329
No, you definitely didn't
tell me about that.

02:46.330 --> 02:48.039
Well, you probably had
a lot on your mind.

02:48.040 --> 02:49.919
♪♪

02:49.920 --> 02:51.289
Do you want to go?

02:51.290 --> 02:52.619
Do you want me to go?

02:52.620 --> 02:53.749
Of course.

02:53.750 --> 02:55.249
Great!
Awesome.

02:55.250 --> 02:56.920
♪♪

03:00.920 --> 03:03.249
Today is problem day.

03:03.250 --> 03:04.789
So you know what that means.

03:04.790 --> 03:06.039
Actually, sir, I-I don't.

03:06.040 --> 03:07.999
Problem spots
on your patrol route.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.829
Locations that attract crime
like a felonious magnet.

03:11.830 --> 03:14.959
Businesses used as a cover
for criminal activity.

03:14.960 --> 03:17.749
No-tell motels,
massage parlors, dive bars.

03:17.750 --> 03:20.919
Or anywhere that ex-cons gather
to plan their next adventure.

03:20.920 --> 03:22.749
The spots you see every day

03:22.750 --> 03:25.079
and you vow to take them down
if you have the time,

03:25.080 --> 03:26.419
but we never have the time.

03:26.420 --> 03:28.880
So... today we make some.

03:32.080 --> 03:33.419
Is there a problem, Smitty?

03:33.420 --> 03:35.169
Oh, no, sir.

03:35.170 --> 03:36.710
I love playing whack-a-mole.

03:38.290 --> 03:41.379
Knock down a problem spot,
it can pop back up anywhere.

03:41.380 --> 03:43.499
But that's the job, right?

03:43.500 --> 03:45.249
And since you're so excited
about doing it,

03:45.250 --> 03:47.079
I think you should share
your excitement

03:47.080 --> 03:48.749
with Officer West
out there today.

03:48.750 --> 03:49.959
Seriously?
Seriously?

03:49.960 --> 03:51.289
Yeah, seriously.

03:51.290 --> 03:53.379
That means, Lopez,
you're with Nolan.

03:53.380 --> 03:56.040
Okay.
Happy hunting out there.

03:59.330 --> 04:00.669
Look, I know
you're probably still mad

04:00.670 --> 04:02.329
about me
not rooming with you, but...

04:02.330 --> 04:04.080
Don't flatter yourself,
sunshine.

04:07.330 --> 04:09.209
So, uh, what's our problem spot?

04:09.210 --> 04:11.710
You'll see when we get there.

04:13.290 --> 04:14.919
So...

04:14.920 --> 04:16.749
what'd you do last night?

04:16.750 --> 04:18.418
Gym. Dinner. Study.

04:18.420 --> 04:20.289
Rinse, wash, repeat.

04:20.290 --> 04:21.540
What's that supposed to mean?

04:22.960 --> 04:24.420
Nothing.

04:27.500 --> 04:28.749
You know, it... it...

04:28.750 --> 04:30.919
It's just been a while
since the divorce.

04:30.920 --> 04:32.669
You wanna jog behind the shop
all day, Boot?

04:32.670 --> 04:33.999
No. No.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.000
No, sir.

04:35.001 --> 04:36.080
Shutting up.

04:37.080 --> 04:38.709
♪♪

04:38.710 --> 04:41.579
It's just a big step,
and it's never come up.

04:41.580 --> 04:43.579
I wasn't prepared,
and now she's mad.

04:43.580 --> 04:45.539
Why do relationships
have to be so complicated?

04:45.540 --> 04:47.459
Some things, you just shouldn't
spring on someone

04:47.460 --> 04:49.329
before they've even had
their morning coffee.

04:49.330 --> 04:51.890
If you can't be honest
with each other, then
why even be together?

04:52.790 --> 04:54.789
And now I'm sitting here
wondering why Wesley
Just, some things
shouldn't be rushed,

04:54.790 --> 04:56.499
doesn't want me
to meet his mom.
and I don't know if I'm ready
to take it to that level.

04:56.500 --> 04:58.119
Wait, what?
I thought we were
talking about my thing.

04:58.120 --> 05:00.539
I thought we were talking
about my thing.

05:00.540 --> 05:02.919
Wesley said he didn't want you
to meet his mom?

05:02.920 --> 05:03.710
He actually said that?

05:03.711 --> 05:05.040
He didn't have to.

05:12.460 --> 05:15.169
"Problem spots," my ass.

05:15.170 --> 05:16.709
What is that smell?

05:16.710 --> 05:19.419
Like sweat socks and licorice.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.379
This whole city's
a problem spot.

05:21.380 --> 05:23.000
Sean John cologne
and desperation.

05:24.710 --> 05:25.999
Pull over at that burger joint.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.289
Seriously?
You just ate a burrito.

05:28.290 --> 05:30.670
That's the problem spot.

05:37.120 --> 05:40.539
Place has been a haven to shady
ex-cons since I was a Boot.

05:40.540 --> 05:42.789
Ain't never gonna change.

05:42.790 --> 05:44.539
So, what do we do?

05:44.540 --> 05:46.249
We sit here. Wait.

05:46.250 --> 05:47.499
For what?

05:47.500 --> 05:48.999
End of shift.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.459
Problem spot. Check.

05:51.460 --> 05:53.829
So, you want us to chill here
in your rank-ass shop?

05:53.830 --> 05:55.919
Rookies.
Ohh.

05:55.920 --> 05:58.500
You all think
you can change the world.

06:11.120 --> 06:12.539
This is our problem spot?

06:12.540 --> 06:13.920
What do you see?

06:18.080 --> 06:19.539
Guy waiting for the bus.

06:19.540 --> 06:21.119
Drug dealer.

06:21.120 --> 06:23.669
This corner's a mecca
for upper-class dopers.

06:23.670 --> 06:25.249
Oxy, Molly, Benzos, Vikes...

06:25.250 --> 06:27.209
Anything a well-off suburbanite
can choke down

06:27.210 --> 06:28.500
with a Kombucha spritzer.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.210
And right on cue.

06:36.460 --> 06:38.209
Gonna bust that dealer?

06:38.210 --> 06:39.619
Buyer. Dealers are
a dime a dozen.

06:39.620 --> 06:41.249
We want to scare
the clients away

06:41.250 --> 06:42.420
so business takes a big hit.

06:54.040 --> 06:55.329
Take the lead on this one.

06:55.330 --> 06:56.540
Okay.

06:58.040 --> 06:59.079
Morning, sir.

06:59.080 --> 07:01.749
What is the problem, officer?

07:01.750 --> 07:03.999
Is it illegal
to ask for directions now?

07:04.000 --> 07:05.250
Well, you better lock me up.

07:07.330 --> 07:08.709
License and registration,
please.

07:08.710 --> 07:11.249
My partner and I witnessed you
exchange money for a baggie.

07:11.250 --> 07:12.459
Wanna show us what you bought?

07:12.460 --> 07:14.749
No idea
what you're talking about.

07:14.750 --> 07:16.249
What's this?

07:16.250 --> 07:18.289
Oops.
How'd that get there?

07:18.290 --> 07:19.959
You work for
Councilwoman Langston?

07:19.960 --> 07:21.379
I'm her right hand.

07:21.380 --> 07:23.500
Sometimes her left,
if you feel me.

07:25.670 --> 07:28.379
Look, Officer, uh... Nolan...

07:28.380 --> 07:29.579
you got a job to do.

07:29.580 --> 07:30.789
I get it.
Believe me.

07:30.790 --> 07:32.829
Nobody appreciates the boys...
And girls...

07:32.830 --> 07:33.879
In blue more than me.

07:33.880 --> 07:37.209
It's just, you see, Langston...

07:37.210 --> 07:39.329
She needed me to find her
some, uh, sleep aids.

07:39.330 --> 07:40.330
Oh. Yeah.

07:40.331 --> 07:41.460
Just hand over the baggie.

07:43.380 --> 07:45.289
No big deal.

07:45.290 --> 07:47.709
Now you, uh, let me off
with a warning,

07:47.710 --> 07:49.379
win yourself
some pretty powerful friends

07:49.380 --> 07:50.579
down at City Hall.

07:50.580 --> 07:52.210
Oh. Sounds like
quite an offer.

07:53.420 --> 07:55.539
Woman:
Councilwoman Langston's office.

07:55.540 --> 07:57.209
But I'm doing okay
in the friend department.

07:57.210 --> 07:58.669
No, no, no. No, no, no.
Uh, um...

07:58.670 --> 08:00.379
Hello?
I'm sorry. T-The pills...
t-t-they're mine.

08:00.380 --> 08:01.880
Hello?
P-P-Please hang up. Please?

08:05.080 --> 08:06.419
I just needed something
to take the edge off.

08:06.420 --> 08:08.379
You can't imagine
what I go through every day.

08:08.380 --> 08:09.789
The wife, boss,
the constant pressure.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.169
It's just...

08:11.170 --> 08:13.000
Jump out of the car.
We're locking you up.

08:16.500 --> 08:17.619
Come over here.
Put your hands on the car.

08:17.620 --> 08:18.620
Yes, sir.

08:20.620 --> 08:22.119
We gonna be here a while?

08:22.120 --> 08:23.329
Yep.

08:23.330 --> 08:25.669
Then I need
to arrange childcare.

08:25.670 --> 08:27.999
Yeah, sure. You get one call
once we're done processing you.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.170
Thanks.

08:31.580 --> 08:34.669
Hey. I know you're
gonna say no, but...

08:35.919 --> 08:38.249
I think I can help.
With what?

08:38.250 --> 08:40.789
Well, you know, I know how hard
it is to meet people in L.A.

08:40.789 --> 08:42.169
It's what keeps them
in business.

08:43.960 --> 08:45.040
Wait.

08:46.710 --> 08:48.040
You wanna set me up?

08:50.080 --> 08:51.289
Forget it.

08:51.290 --> 08:53.619
Even if this wasn't
your dumbest idea yet,

08:53.620 --> 08:56.710
there is no way you'd be able
to pick someone right for me.

08:57.750 --> 08:59.959
Um, I bet I can.

08:59.960 --> 09:01.579
I'm serious.

09:01.580 --> 09:04.169
If I can fix you up
on one good date, just one,

09:04.170 --> 09:06.289
I get to, uh...

09:06.290 --> 09:07.829
I get to wear short sleeves.

09:07.830 --> 09:13.579
♪♪

09:13.580 --> 09:14.669
Okay.

09:14.670 --> 09:16.579
Okay.

09:16.580 --> 09:18.209
But you're paying.
Whatever.

09:18.210 --> 09:20.669
And if you lose,
you're gonna do 50 push-ups

09:20.670 --> 09:22.380
after every call we take.

09:26.210 --> 09:28.330
♪ Hey! ♪
♪ Show me something
that I never seen before ♪

09:30.380 --> 09:32.040
♪ Oh oh ♪

09:34.830 --> 09:36.829
Okay. New plan.

09:36.830 --> 09:39.460
You drink your soda, and I'm
gonna go do some policing.

09:42.120 --> 09:43.120
Here they come.

09:43.120 --> 09:44.120
Keep cool.

09:47.040 --> 09:48.789
Morning, officers.
Smitty: Boys.

09:48.790 --> 09:50.329
My partner here is a newbie

09:50.330 --> 09:52.879
who wants to learn about
problem spots in town.

09:52.880 --> 09:53.919
So here we are.

09:53.920 --> 09:55.209
I'm just eating.

09:55.210 --> 09:56.579
Sure you are.

09:56.580 --> 09:58.289
Danny Dozier.

09:58.290 --> 09:59.959
You just did four years
in Chino.

09:59.960 --> 10:01.210
Armed robbery, was it?

10:03.210 --> 10:05.039
And you.

10:05.040 --> 10:07.539
Weren't you the wheelman
for Larry Marks?

10:07.540 --> 10:10.749
Think of this as
a lowlife employment agency.

10:10.750 --> 10:14.039
Each of these dirtbags has
a set of illicit skills,

10:14.040 --> 10:16.169
and they are just itching
for a chance to use 'em.

10:16.170 --> 10:17.919
Hmm.
Last time I checked,

10:17.920 --> 10:20.619
associating with felons was
a no-no for parolees.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.289
Raise your hand
if you're on parole.

10:23.290 --> 10:25.079
Look, don't make me
run you through the system.

10:25.080 --> 10:26.540
It'll just piss me off.

10:28.040 --> 10:29.579
There we go.
That's more like it.

10:29.580 --> 10:31.119
Everybody grab some wall.

10:31.120 --> 10:33.540
Come on.
Right this way.

10:37.000 --> 10:38.120
Speed it up.

10:42.080 --> 10:43.329
Smitty:
What are you doing?

10:43.330 --> 10:44.959
Just kick 'em loose
with a warning.

10:44.960 --> 10:46.169
Tell them not to come back.

10:46.170 --> 10:48.079
Problem spot handled.

10:48.080 --> 10:50.080
They break the law, they go in.

10:52.120 --> 10:55.329
♪♪

10:55.330 --> 10:56.499
Go, kid.

10:56.500 --> 11:00.249
♪♪

11:00.250 --> 11:01.539
Foot pursuit.

11:01.540 --> 11:03.169
White male,
gray shirt and blue jeans,

11:03.170 --> 11:05.289
headed north on Fillmore.

11:05.290 --> 11:07.249
♪ Looking around,
and I don't know why ♪

11:07.250 --> 11:08.829
♪ But they held me ♪

11:08.830 --> 11:12.880
♪ If you watch him cry and you
don't know why, then... ♪

11:33.540 --> 11:40.289
♪♪

11:40.290 --> 11:46.790
♪♪

11:48.670 --> 11:50.750
♪♪

11:51.960 --> 11:53.669
Why'd you run, huh?

11:53.670 --> 11:54.750
Stand up.

11:56.120 --> 11:58.419
Spread your feet.

11:58.420 --> 12:00.289
♪♪

12:00.290 --> 12:01.419
Where's the gun?

12:01.420 --> 12:03.209
I don't got one.
I just like bullets.

12:03.210 --> 12:04.330
That ain't a crime, is it?

12:05.790 --> 12:07.619
He must have dumped the gun
somewhere between here
and the burger joint.

12:07.620 --> 12:09.039
Woman: Help!

12:09.040 --> 12:10.749
Somebody please help me!

12:10.750 --> 12:12.749
I need help!
Please, somebody!

12:12.750 --> 12:14.579
Calvin, g...

12:14.580 --> 12:16.119
Calvin!
Give me the gun, baby.

12:16.120 --> 12:17.709
Baby, please.
Give me the gun.

12:17.710 --> 12:18.749
Calvin!

12:18.750 --> 12:19.750
Hey, Calvin?

12:19.751 --> 12:21.749
Buddy.
It's not a toy, okay?

12:21.750 --> 12:23.169
Please put the gun down.

12:23.170 --> 12:24.499
Calvin, give me the gun!

12:24.500 --> 12:26.079
Hey, buddy,
please put the gun down.

12:26.080 --> 12:28.200
Calvin, give me the gun!
It's not a toy!
Put the gun...

12:33.420 --> 12:34.940
Gunshot wound
to the upper-right chest!

12:44.000 --> 12:48.999
♪♪

12:49.000 --> 12:50.079
You did this.

12:50.080 --> 12:51.080
I didn't do nothin'.

12:51.080 --> 12:52.080
It was your gun!

12:53.210 --> 12:54.330
Prove it.

13:01.250 --> 13:02.289
Rachel?

13:02.290 --> 13:04.119
Look at you!

13:04.120 --> 13:06.669
Oh, my G... All official!

13:06.670 --> 13:08.289
Mm!
Mm!

13:08.290 --> 13:10.419
You were the talk
of the reunion, you know.

13:10.420 --> 13:11.749
I was bummed I couldn't go.

13:11.750 --> 13:12.919
What are you doing here?

13:12.920 --> 13:15.459
Oh, just trying to cut through
some red tape.

13:15.460 --> 13:18.039
But so far, my scissors
haven't been sharp enough.

13:18.040 --> 13:19.539
Oh, problems in Child Services?

13:19.540 --> 13:21.169
Yeah, civil standbys.

13:21.170 --> 13:23.499
LAPD needs
a faster response time.

13:23.500 --> 13:25.619
I've had four go sideways
in the last month.

13:25.620 --> 13:26.620
Mm.

13:27.620 --> 13:30.119
Hey.
Maybe you can help me.

13:30.120 --> 13:32.209
I-I wish I could,

13:32.210 --> 13:34.209
but I am below
bottom of the food chain here.

13:34.210 --> 13:35.210
It's...

13:35.211 --> 13:36.789
Boot! Get a move on.

13:36.790 --> 13:38.540
No lunch till you finish
those reports.

13:39.790 --> 13:40.790
Who's that?

13:40.791 --> 13:42.999
That is my training officer.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.330
I should probably go.

13:46.960 --> 13:49.419
Hey, uh, you're single, right?

13:49.420 --> 13:50.669
Mm-hmm.

13:50.670 --> 13:52.709
Would you want
to go out with him?

13:52.710 --> 13:55.079
Uh, he's hot...

13:55.080 --> 13:57.209
but I-I made a vow.

13:57.210 --> 13:58.379
No more jerks.

13:58.380 --> 13:59.790
Tim: Let's go, Boot!

14:01.040 --> 14:03.999
Okay, so, you don't date jerks.

14:04.000 --> 14:06.879
But how would you like to
help me win a bet against one?

14:06.880 --> 14:08.830
♪♪

14:11.880 --> 14:13.289
Smitty: Let's go.

14:13.290 --> 14:15.789
We gotta take this dirtbag
back to the station,

14:15.790 --> 14:17.210
get him processed.

14:19.710 --> 14:20.960
You alright?

14:22.000 --> 14:23.120
No.

14:24.620 --> 14:26.709
I...

14:26.710 --> 14:29.499
I should have tackled the kid.

14:29.500 --> 14:30.750
Taken the bullet myself.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.879
That's a no-win situation.

14:36.880 --> 14:38.619
Had you reacted differently,

14:38.620 --> 14:41.669
maybe the kid would have
shot himself instead.

14:41.670 --> 14:42.880
Hey.

14:44.580 --> 14:46.620
You did the right thing.

14:48.210 --> 14:49.530
Yeah, it was... it wasn't enough.

14:51.750 --> 14:52.999
Hey, Jess.

14:53.000 --> 14:55.959
It's me.
Just trying you... again.

14:55.960 --> 14:57.999
Call me back.

14:58.000 --> 14:59.459
Okay.

14:59.460 --> 15:04.170
She is definitely mad at me
and ducking my calls.

15:06.170 --> 15:07.539
What time is dinner with Mom?

15:07.540 --> 15:08.709
Huh?
Dinner.

15:08.710 --> 15:10.579
Oh. Um...

15:10.580 --> 15:11.619
At 8:00, I think.

15:11.620 --> 15:13.249
You know, there is no world

15:13.250 --> 15:14.920
in which
Wesley is embarrassed by you.

15:16.380 --> 15:19.039
If that was
what you were worried about.

15:19.040 --> 15:20.919
It's not.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.999
Park:
I'm not charging him.

15:23.000 --> 15:24.419
You're kidding me.
Why not?

15:24.420 --> 15:26.169
You never saw the gun
in his possession,

15:26.170 --> 15:27.539
and his prints weren't on it.

15:27.540 --> 15:28.999
All you got was
a pocket full of bullets.

15:29.000 --> 15:30.379
There's no crime in that.

15:30.380 --> 15:31.789
Bullets are the same caliber
as the gun.

15:31.790 --> 15:34.379
It's a 9-millimeter.
Most common handgun there is.

15:34.380 --> 15:35.959
He tossed the gun
while I was chasing him,

15:35.960 --> 15:37.539
and a child picked it up.

15:37.540 --> 15:39.079
But you didn't see it.

15:39.080 --> 15:40.169
That kid could've
killed himself.

15:40.170 --> 15:41.959
As it is,
his mother almost died.

15:41.960 --> 15:43.249
The kid is traumatized.

15:43.250 --> 15:45.169
So how in the hell
can you kick this guy loose?

15:45.170 --> 15:46.879
It's not a case that we can win.
I'm sorry.

15:46.880 --> 15:48.000
I have to get back to court.

15:57.080 --> 15:58.499
Don't call her again.

15:58.500 --> 15:59.919
When she's ready,
she'll call you.

15:59.920 --> 16:01.460
You're right.

16:06.500 --> 16:07.579
Turn around.
What?

16:07.580 --> 16:09.060
There's a guy back there
being chased.

16:11.040 --> 16:13.789
Control 7-Adam-15, suspicious
circs on 5th and Beaudry,

16:13.790 --> 16:15.080
requesting backup.

16:17.330 --> 16:20.500
♪♪

16:22.960 --> 16:25.459
Back up! Back up!
Move your vehicle!

16:25.460 --> 16:27.619
Come on! Come on, damn it!

16:27.620 --> 16:30.710
♪♪

16:33.000 --> 16:37.079
♪♪

16:37.080 --> 16:39.080
You see them?
There.

16:41.460 --> 16:49.460
♪♪

16:58.540 --> 16:59.919
Back seat clear.

16:59.920 --> 17:01.169
Front seat clear.

17:01.170 --> 17:02.749
So, where'd they go?

17:02.750 --> 17:03.960
Head upstai...

17:05.710 --> 17:08.079
♪♪

17:11.750 --> 17:13.789
Man: Coming through.
Out of the way!

17:13.790 --> 17:15.039
We're over here.

17:15.040 --> 17:16.378
What do we have?

17:16.380 --> 17:18.459
Patient suffered
a fractured left femur,

17:18.460 --> 17:19.709
possible internal bleeding,
and head trauma.

17:19.710 --> 17:21.169
- BP?
- Stable.

17:21.170 --> 17:22.919
They gave him two liters
of saline on the way over.

17:22.920 --> 17:23.999
- Hi.
- Hey.

17:24.000 --> 17:25.289
What happened to him?
Car accident?

17:25.290 --> 17:27.378
No, no. He, uh, got
dropped off a footbridge.

17:27.380 --> 17:28.999
Landed on top of a car
right in front of us.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.249
Do you know his name?

17:30.250 --> 17:32.329
Uh, yeah, driver's license
says he's Cesar Ojeda.

17:32.330 --> 17:34.289
Okay. We need a CT scan.
Alert the OR.

17:34.290 --> 17:36.209
He's jumping the line.
Not before I talk to him.

17:36.210 --> 17:38.289
Jessica Russo. DHS.
Hey.

17:38.290 --> 17:39.789
That's not possible.

17:39.790 --> 17:41.329
Well, make it possible.

17:41.330 --> 17:43.039
He's unconscious and probably
bleeding internally.

17:43.040 --> 17:44.619
If we delay surgery,
he could die.

17:44.620 --> 17:45.620
Is that what you want?

17:45.621 --> 17:46.709
Nobody wants that, right?

17:46.710 --> 17:47.789
N-No.

17:47.790 --> 17:49.419
I... Fine. Fine.

17:49.420 --> 17:51.119
I just need to talk to him
as soon as he wakes up.

17:51.120 --> 17:52.460
Of course.
Let's move.

17:56.290 --> 17:57.499
So, who was that guy,

17:57.500 --> 18:00.079
and why did you have to
talk to him so badly?

18:00.080 --> 18:01.539
I can't really tell you that.

18:01.540 --> 18:02.879
Can't or won't?

18:02.880 --> 18:04.789
I ran the plates
on the car that chased him.

18:04.790 --> 18:06.079
It was reported stolen
last week.

18:06.080 --> 18:07.789
What about the guys inside?

18:07.790 --> 18:09.499
They were gone by the time
backup cleared the building.

18:09.500 --> 18:10.670
What's your interest?

18:13.080 --> 18:15.539
His real name
is Alejandro Mejia.

18:15.540 --> 18:17.379
He's undercover DHS.

18:17.380 --> 18:20.329
He disappeared about six weeks
ago during an infiltration,

18:20.330 --> 18:23.249
and I was alerted when you ran
his cover ID through the system.

18:23.250 --> 18:25.209
Wow.
So, what was he into?

18:25.210 --> 18:27.209
I-I'm not cleared
to tell you that.

18:27.210 --> 18:29.209
So, DHS is taking this over?

18:29.210 --> 18:30.959
Yes, but I would really
appreciate it

18:30.960 --> 18:32.579
if you could provide
some extra security

18:32.580 --> 18:34.039
until my guys got here.

18:34.040 --> 18:34.880
Of course.

18:34.881 --> 18:36.209
Excuse me.

18:36.210 --> 18:38.379
Yes, sir?

18:38.380 --> 18:40.289
Yeah, she's definitely
mad at you.

18:40.290 --> 18:43.119
Yes, he's, um...
He's unconscious and...

18:43.120 --> 18:44.419
She's a social worker?

18:44.420 --> 18:46.499
You say that
like it's equivalent

18:46.500 --> 18:48.119
to being a serial killer.

18:48.120 --> 18:49.959
No. Social workers
do valuable work...

18:49.960 --> 18:50.960
Coddling criminals.

18:52.080 --> 18:54.539
Look, if you're not
even gonna try...
Hold your water, Boot.

18:54.540 --> 18:56.579
I'm just getting
the lay of the land
on my "date."

18:56.580 --> 18:58.169
So, where
are you taking her?
Ravenna.

18:58.170 --> 19:00.579
That... sounds expensive.

19:00.580 --> 19:02.209
Oh. It is.

19:02.210 --> 19:05.539
They've got a $100 filet,
just melts in your mouth.

19:05.540 --> 19:07.919
And their wine list... ohh!
It's exceptional.

19:07.920 --> 19:09.169
Well, good.

19:09.170 --> 19:11.669
It seems like
a really romantic place.

19:11.670 --> 19:13.169
Hmm.
What?

19:13.170 --> 19:15.500
You're gonna have to do
so many push-ups.

19:16.960 --> 19:19.959
Anyway, this... is Rachel.

19:19.960 --> 19:22.959
♪♪

19:22.960 --> 19:24.419
Pretty.

19:24.420 --> 19:25.879
Wes, where's Smitty?

19:25.880 --> 19:28.329
Probably watching "Judge Judy"
in the break room.

19:28.330 --> 19:30.459
Sir, was pairing us up
meant to be added punishment?

19:30.460 --> 19:32.459
Think of it
more as a kick in the pants.

19:32.460 --> 19:34.249
No way you're advancing
back to short sleeves

19:34.250 --> 19:36.209
until I see the fire
back in your eyes.

19:36.210 --> 19:38.919
You collared a guy named
Gleason Dunn earlier, right?

19:38.920 --> 19:40.289
Yeah.

19:40.290 --> 19:41.829
You ship him downtown yet?

19:41.830 --> 19:43.499
No, he's, uh,
being processed out.

19:43.500 --> 19:44.460
ADA told me to kick him.

19:44.461 --> 19:45.829
Why?

19:45.830 --> 19:47.879
Ballistics came back
on the gun the kid fired.

19:47.880 --> 19:50.210
It was used in
an unsolved murder last year.

19:51.500 --> 19:52.579
What?

19:52.580 --> 19:54.249
They pulled a DNA sample
from the scene,

19:54.250 --> 19:56.209
but there was no match
in the system.

19:56.210 --> 19:58.829
Dunn's DNA isn't in the system.
We don't have it.

19:58.830 --> 20:00.030
Well, we need to get a sample.

20:03.880 --> 20:11.880
♪♪

20:12.580 --> 20:14.709
Excuse me.

20:14.710 --> 20:16.379
Gleason Dunn.

20:16.380 --> 20:17.419
Where is he?

20:17.420 --> 20:19.669
Released.
About 10 minutes ago.

20:19.670 --> 20:23.039
♪♪

20:23.040 --> 20:25.120
Okay.
I'm... I'm on my way in.

20:28.000 --> 20:29.209
Hey.

20:29.210 --> 20:30.210
Hey.

20:30.211 --> 20:31.789
So, about this morning...

20:31.790 --> 20:33.669
Oh. This is
not the right time.

20:33.670 --> 20:35.249
Right.
Yeah.

20:35.250 --> 20:37.669
And also, I mean,
it's not a big deal.

20:37.670 --> 20:39.249
So we're good?

20:39.250 --> 20:41.879
Yeah. Uh,
why wouldn't we be?

20:41.880 --> 20:42.959
Right.

20:42.960 --> 20:44.379
I brought Grey up to speed.

20:44.380 --> 20:45.539
He said he'd give you
whatever you need.

20:45.540 --> 20:46.829
Oh, great.

20:46.830 --> 20:48.329
Any chance
you got more clearance

20:48.330 --> 20:49.829
to tell us about Mejia?
Yes.

20:49.830 --> 20:53.619
He's a forensic accountant,
an expert in cryptocurrency.

20:53.620 --> 20:55.709
We put him inside
an illegal arms operation,

20:55.710 --> 20:58.329
where he was supposed to
target their financials

20:58.330 --> 21:00.329
and then neutralize
their access.

21:00.330 --> 21:02.079
By what?
Changing all their passwords?

21:02.080 --> 21:03.329
Basically, yeah.

21:03.330 --> 21:05.579
The downside of digital money.

21:05.580 --> 21:07.709
Then Mejia went silent, what'd
you say, about six weeks ago?

21:07.710 --> 21:08.999
Mm-hmm.

21:09.000 --> 21:10.669
So we presumed
he was either dead or...

21:10.670 --> 21:11.919
Compromised.

21:11.920 --> 21:13.329
No wonder
you need to talk to him.

21:13.330 --> 21:15.619
Look, um,
I've got to go brief my boss.

21:15.620 --> 21:18.999
DHS is gonna be mobilizing
some agents to come stand watch.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.789
Are you good until they arrive?

21:20.790 --> 21:23.079
Like Grey said,
anything you need.

21:23.080 --> 21:24.959
Hmm.

21:24.960 --> 21:26.539
Alright, I'm gonna
take the shop.

21:26.540 --> 21:28.669
Dispatch will arrange pickup
once you're replaced.

21:28.670 --> 21:30.499
You're leaving?
I gotta get dressed
for dinner.

21:30.500 --> 21:32.289
The great thing about you
being a phase three now

21:32.290 --> 21:34.119
is I don't have to
supervise you 24-7.

21:34.120 --> 21:35.419
So have fun on guard duty.

21:35.420 --> 21:36.920
Good luck with Mommie Dearest.

21:43.170 --> 21:46.829
I briefed my buddies
on Midnight shift about Gleason.

21:46.830 --> 21:47.920
They'll get him.

21:51.170 --> 21:53.039
You know, it's not too late.

21:53.040 --> 21:54.209
For what?

21:54.210 --> 21:56.169
Scale of 1 to 10,
how sure are you

21:56.170 --> 21:57.539
the gun belonged to Gleason?

21:57.540 --> 21:58.879
10.

21:58.880 --> 22:01.380
Then maybe you need to revise
your statement to the ADA.

22:02.710 --> 22:05.959
You're a rookie whose vision
got blurry in the fog of war,

22:05.960 --> 22:07.619
but now you're clear,

22:07.620 --> 22:09.170
and you did see him
toss the weapon.

22:10.420 --> 22:12.540
Write it up like that,
and I'll back you.

22:15.670 --> 22:23.579
♪♪

22:23.580 --> 22:25.000
I'd be lying.

22:26.580 --> 22:30.079
Kid, you're in the honeymoon
period of being a cop.

22:30.080 --> 22:32.169
Full of piss
and righteous vinegar.

22:32.170 --> 22:34.039
But it's not
a black-and-white world.

22:34.040 --> 22:35.169
Never has been.

22:35.170 --> 22:37.789
Look, right and wrong matter.

22:37.790 --> 22:39.669
Otherwise, why bother
pinning on the badge?

22:39.670 --> 22:40.999
It's not about right and wrong.

22:41.000 --> 22:43.999
It's about getting the bad guys
off the street.

22:44.000 --> 22:46.209
How you gonna feel
if we can't pin Gleason down

22:46.210 --> 22:47.999
and he hurts more people?

22:48.000 --> 22:49.209
Or worse.

22:49.210 --> 22:51.709
It can't be worse than today.

22:51.710 --> 22:53.170
Oh, it can always get worse.

22:56.540 --> 22:58.499
Yeah?

22:58.500 --> 23:00.750
Okay, thanks.

23:04.080 --> 23:06.250
The mom died
on the operating table.

23:07.750 --> 23:09.580
I'm sorry.

23:17.790 --> 23:19.459
Lucy: Yes!

23:19.460 --> 23:22.289
I'm so glad she wore that dress.

23:22.290 --> 23:23.709
She didn't want to look
too sexy,

23:23.710 --> 23:26.880
but, uh, Mama needs to get
into some short sleeves.

23:29.250 --> 23:31.169
Yo.
Where did you go?

23:31.170 --> 23:33.539
Sorry. Uh...

23:33.540 --> 23:35.379
I can't stop thinking
about my guy.

23:35.380 --> 23:38.209
He killed someone,
and I just let him walk.

23:38.210 --> 23:40.379
Dude, you did
what the ADA told you to do,

23:40.380 --> 23:42.289
and now you're trying to fix it.

23:42.290 --> 23:43.829
Night shift is on the hunt.

23:43.830 --> 23:45.209
Yeah.

23:45.210 --> 23:47.289
Head in the game.
Let's go.

23:47.290 --> 23:48.619
This is so weird.

23:48.620 --> 23:49.669
Uh-huh.
Yep, yep, yep.

23:49.670 --> 23:51.209
♪♪

23:51.210 --> 23:54.959
So, you've, uh...
You've known Chen since...

23:54.960 --> 23:57.119
I mean, Lucy since college?

23:57.120 --> 23:59.459
Yeah, we were
in psych class together.

23:59.460 --> 24:00.829
Hmm.

24:00.830 --> 24:02.119
Bet she hasn't changed a bit.

24:02.120 --> 24:04.999
No. Always playing
matchmaker.

24:05.000 --> 24:06.789
Well, this is my favorite place.

24:06.790 --> 24:08.539
Best filet in town.

24:08.540 --> 24:10.709
Oh, I don't eat red meat.

24:10.710 --> 24:12.039
Sea bass is great, too.

24:12.040 --> 24:14.039
Nothing that had a face.

24:14.040 --> 24:16.579
I'm on a raw-food diet,
actually.

24:16.580 --> 24:19.249
You know, reduce my imprint.

24:19.250 --> 24:20.959
♪ This is roller coaster love ♪

24:20.960 --> 24:23.419
♪ Leave you breathless
every time ♪

24:23.420 --> 24:25.879
Lucy: Oh, wait.
What happened?

24:25.880 --> 24:26.880
They stopped talking.

24:29.290 --> 24:31.459
Jackson: This is like watching
a nature documentary.

24:31.460 --> 24:33.900
You're just waiting
for the gazelle to get
eaten by the jaguar.

24:37.420 --> 24:39.459
Oh, my God.

24:39.460 --> 24:40.999
I'm gonna lose this bet.

24:41.000 --> 24:42.879
Pbht.

24:42.880 --> 24:45.329
Look, you seem nice and all,

24:45.330 --> 24:47.539
so I probably should just
tell you the truth.

24:47.540 --> 24:51.419
I let Lucy set us up tonight
because she made me a bet.

24:51.420 --> 24:54.209
And, um, you want her to lose.

24:54.210 --> 24:56.789
No, I want me to win.

24:56.790 --> 24:59.209
Being here with me isn't a win?

24:59.210 --> 25:02.000
♪ Love me
till I say I want more ♪

25:03.460 --> 25:04.499
Maybe a little.

25:04.500 --> 25:06.419
Mm-hmm.

25:06.420 --> 25:08.539
♪♪

25:08.540 --> 25:10.709
You know what would be
a win for me?

25:10.710 --> 25:12.999
♪♪

25:13.000 --> 25:15.170
If you could get me...

25:17.500 --> 25:20.579
a direct line
to your watch commander

25:20.580 --> 25:22.879
so I could talk to him
about civil standbys.

25:22.880 --> 25:25.539
♪ Leave you breathless
every time ♪

25:25.540 --> 25:31.879
♪♪

25:31.880 --> 25:33.379
I could do that.

25:33.380 --> 25:34.919
Really?

25:34.920 --> 25:36.209
Yeah.

25:36.210 --> 25:38.169
And what would you want
in return?

25:38.170 --> 25:40.000
♪ Who could it be? ♪

25:43.080 --> 25:47.209
♪♪

25:47.210 --> 25:49.619
I'm gonna be
in long sleeves forever.

25:49.620 --> 25:52.920
♪♪

25:55.250 --> 25:57.329
Where am I?

25:57.330 --> 25:59.119
You're in the hospital,
Mr. Mejia.

25:59.120 --> 26:00.919
You just underwent surgery.

26:00.920 --> 26:01.959
You know my name?

26:01.960 --> 26:03.249
Yes, I do.

26:03.250 --> 26:05.499
I'm working with DHS...
Jessica Russo.

26:05.500 --> 26:07.539
She told us about
your undercover op.

26:07.540 --> 26:09.289
Looks like you have
quite a tale to tell.

26:09.290 --> 26:10.579
I need to get outta here.

26:10.580 --> 26:11.619
Not just yet.

26:11.620 --> 26:13.289
You've been through
a great deal.

26:13.290 --> 26:15.619
Um, the men
who were chasing you...

26:15.620 --> 26:16.620
Can you ID them?

26:17.920 --> 26:19.289
No.

26:19.290 --> 26:20.669
Why did they throw you
off the bridge?

26:20.670 --> 26:22.499
They didn't.
I jumped.

26:22.500 --> 26:23.749
Why?

26:23.750 --> 26:25.289
Seemed necessary at the time.

26:25.290 --> 26:26.789
Were they trying to kill you?

26:26.790 --> 26:28.619
Worse.

26:28.620 --> 26:30.750
What do you mean by that?

26:31.580 --> 26:32.880
Mr. Mejia?

26:35.250 --> 26:37.670
Come on. We got to
get to my mom's party.

26:38.710 --> 26:39.919
No.

26:39.920 --> 26:41.499
Not until you admit

26:41.500 --> 26:43.249
you never mentioned
this thing with your mom before.

26:43.250 --> 26:44.960
I-I thought I did.

26:48.380 --> 26:49.789
Okay, fine. I didn't.

26:49.790 --> 26:51.249
I knew it.
You didn't want her to meet me.

26:51.250 --> 26:52.499
Angela.

26:52.500 --> 26:54.709
Is it because I'm...
spirited?

26:54.710 --> 26:56.879
No.
You got us a chess clock
to mediate our arguments.

26:56.880 --> 26:58.209
I know, but that's not
what this...

26:58.210 --> 27:00.709
And I can be a little feral
when I eat sometimes, but...

27:00.710 --> 27:01.790
Angela.

27:03.880 --> 27:06.080
This wasn't about you.

27:07.790 --> 27:08.920
What does that mean?

27:10.790 --> 27:14.079
Look, I have to
tell you something...

27:14.080 --> 27:16.000
but I don't want you
to freak out.

27:19.710 --> 27:20.829
You're rich.

27:20.830 --> 27:23.120
Well, wealth is relative.

27:24.120 --> 27:25.879
Yeah. Super rich.

27:25.880 --> 27:29.419
Oh, look who decided
to grace us with his presence.

27:29.420 --> 27:30.420
Hello, darling.

27:31.540 --> 27:33.289
Hello, my dear!
Hi.

27:33.290 --> 27:36.289
Oh, it's so nice
to finally meet you.

27:36.290 --> 27:37.879
You are simply stunning.

27:37.880 --> 27:39.709
Thank you.
You are, too, Mrs. Evers.

27:39.710 --> 27:41.329
And... And this beautiful house.

27:41.330 --> 27:42.919
Come on.
Let's get you a drink.

27:42.920 --> 27:45.619
♪ It feels like flying ♪

27:45.620 --> 27:48.289
♪♪

27:48.290 --> 27:51.169
So, what made you decide
to become a police officer?

27:51.170 --> 27:53.119
Well, I love my city
and wanted to give back.

27:53.120 --> 27:55.120
Mm.
Getting to kick ass
helped, too.

27:56.580 --> 27:59.329
Well, I, for one,
thank you for your service.

27:59.330 --> 28:03.039
You know, you put 'em in jail,
and my son tries to get 'em out.

28:03.040 --> 28:04.539
Mother.

28:04.540 --> 28:06.209
Why do you keep
calling me "Mother,"

28:06.210 --> 28:07.879
like... like this is
"Downton Abbey"?

28:07.880 --> 28:08.959
Insufferable, isn't he?

28:08.960 --> 28:10.169
Definitely, but he's cute.

28:10.170 --> 28:12.379
You know,
his grandfather founded

28:12.380 --> 28:14.619
the biggest law firm
in Beverly Hills,

28:14.620 --> 28:17.879
but Wesley insists
on working pro bono,

28:17.880 --> 28:20.789
over a restaurant
that serves $5.99 buffets.

28:20.790 --> 28:21.790
Mother.

28:22.750 --> 28:24.249
Mom.

28:24.250 --> 28:26.079
Well, I just want to give you
a helping hand

28:26.080 --> 28:27.879
from time to time,
but you slap it away.

28:27.880 --> 28:29.289
Well, I do fine on my own.

28:29.290 --> 28:31.169
But you could do so much more.

28:31.170 --> 28:34.039
Okay, can we not talk about this
right now, in front of Angela?

28:34.040 --> 28:38.079
But you're living together.
She's family.

28:38.080 --> 28:39.829
And, you know,
there's never really a good time

28:39.830 --> 28:41.289
to talk with you.

28:41.290 --> 28:42.879
I-I know you want
to do it all on your own

28:42.880 --> 28:44.039
and not touch your trust fund...

28:44.040 --> 28:45.579
Trust fund?

28:45.580 --> 28:47.669
But the fact that you seem
mad at me about it,

28:47.670 --> 28:49.209
that is just messed up.

28:49.210 --> 28:50.499
How's your wine?

28:50.500 --> 28:52.169
Amazing.

28:52.170 --> 28:54.749
Yeah, I picked it up
at a spa retreat in Tuscany.

28:54.750 --> 28:56.039
I'm going again in March.

28:56.040 --> 28:57.499
You should come.

28:57.500 --> 28:58.709
Wesley, you two should come.

28:58.710 --> 29:00.079
100% yes.
Yes.

29:00.080 --> 29:02.039
Mm. You know what?

29:02.040 --> 29:03.160
I'm gonna take an Uber home.

29:04.120 --> 29:05.959
The two of you, just...

29:05.960 --> 29:07.000
enjoy each other.

29:08.000 --> 29:09.749
Come on, Wesley.

29:09.750 --> 29:11.169
Always with the drama.

29:11.170 --> 29:12.579
I should go after him.

29:12.580 --> 29:15.079
Oh, nonsense.
He's a grown man.

29:15.080 --> 29:17.579
Besides, I want you
to taste the stew.

29:17.580 --> 29:19.290
It's my own recipe.

29:21.080 --> 29:22.289
It does smell good.

29:22.290 --> 29:23.290
Mm-hmm.

29:27.170 --> 29:28.289
Hi.

29:28.290 --> 29:30.169
I'm here to transfer
the patient to the ICU

29:30.170 --> 29:32.329
for some serial exams,
check for any internal bleeding.

29:32.330 --> 29:34.669
Sure.
Uh, do you mind if I...?
Sure.

29:34.670 --> 29:36.669
Susan Taylor. How long
have you worked here, Susan?

29:36.670 --> 29:38.289
A lot of fives.

29:38.290 --> 29:40.789
Five months in the ICU,
five years at the hospital,

29:40.790 --> 29:43.039
and, uh, since 5:00
this morning...

29:43.040 --> 29:44.539
5:30, actually...

29:44.540 --> 29:45.749
Okay, well, I'm gonna need
to accompany you.

29:45.750 --> 29:47.000
No problem.

29:48.120 --> 29:50.249
Why do I do this?
Do what?

29:50.250 --> 29:52.539
Infiltrate myself
into everything.

29:52.540 --> 29:53.749
I'm like a virus.

29:53.750 --> 29:54.829
You're not a virus.

29:54.830 --> 29:56.249
Yes. I am.

29:56.250 --> 29:58.209
Why do I care if Tim dates?

29:58.210 --> 30:00.619
Why do I care
why anyone does anything?

30:00.620 --> 30:02.709
Okay, you just want
everyone to be happy.
That's a good quality.

30:02.710 --> 30:04.669
No, you know what I want?
To get drunk.

30:04.670 --> 30:06.789
Let's get a butt load
of tequila,

30:06.790 --> 30:07.959
get up on the roof
of our building,

30:07.960 --> 30:09.379
and listen to music
from the Hollywood Bowl.

30:09.380 --> 30:10.499
That's what I want.

30:10.500 --> 30:12.249
Hello?

30:12.250 --> 30:13.379
Yeah.

30:13.380 --> 30:15.709
♪♪

30:15.710 --> 30:17.079
Thank you for letting me know.

30:17.080 --> 30:18.249
What was that?

30:18.250 --> 30:20.329
Night shift
still hasn't found Gleason.

30:20.330 --> 30:21.959
Bastard's still
walking around out there.

30:21.960 --> 30:23.120
Give 'em time.

30:25.170 --> 30:26.289
What are you doing?

30:26.290 --> 30:27.829
Getting my car.
I'm going for a ride.

30:27.830 --> 30:30.119
Going for a ride up the PCH
with a little bit of sad music

30:30.120 --> 30:31.710
or a little off-duty action?

30:33.500 --> 30:34.619
Okay. I'll drive.

30:34.620 --> 30:37.169
Hey, Jess.

30:37.170 --> 30:39.249
Oh, yeah, well, no,
he was a-awake for a minute,

30:39.250 --> 30:41.169
and now he's unconscious again.

30:41.170 --> 30:43.669
They're just transferring him
to ICU.

30:43.670 --> 30:45.830
Right. Okay.
I'll see you in a few.

30:47.960 --> 30:49.169
How's it going?

30:49.170 --> 30:50.749
Good. Yeah, good.

30:50.750 --> 30:52.619
Uh, Jessica's on her way here
to question him.

30:52.620 --> 30:54.619
It... seems like
you know her pretty well.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.539
Yeah.
Well, we're dating.

30:56.540 --> 30:58.119
Really?

30:58.120 --> 30:59.169
What?

30:59.170 --> 31:00.999
Nothing.

31:01.000 --> 31:02.419
She's j...
She's a little intense.

31:02.420 --> 31:04.669
Oh, that's...
just "work Jessica."

31:04.670 --> 31:06.289
Yeah, she's...
She's different at home.

31:06.290 --> 31:07.290
Sure.

31:07.291 --> 31:09.169
What?
Nothing. Um...

31:09.170 --> 31:11.539
She just... She doesn't
really seem like your type.

31:11.540 --> 31:12.919
My type?

31:12.920 --> 31:14.379
Never mind. You know what?
I'm gonna shut up.

31:14.380 --> 31:17.120
People can change a lot
in 20 years.

31:18.750 --> 31:20.829
W-What are you doing
outside the ICU?

31:20.830 --> 31:23.079
Oh, uh, the nurse transferred
Mejia here from post-op.

31:23.080 --> 31:24.280
They needed to run some tests.

31:25.460 --> 31:26.579
But I just...
I spoke with the surgeon.

31:26.580 --> 31:28.329
He didn't want
to move Mejia yet.

31:28.330 --> 31:30.169
He was gonna do the exams
in post-op.

31:30.170 --> 31:36.080
♪♪

31:40.380 --> 31:43.709
♪♪

31:43.710 --> 31:45.789
I need this hospital put
on immediate lockdown!

31:45.790 --> 31:47.209
Nobody in or out.

31:47.210 --> 31:49.249
7-Adam-15, 207 at Shaw Memorial.

31:49.250 --> 31:50.879
I need backup,
unknown number of suspects,

31:50.880 --> 31:52.210
possibly armed, Code 3.

32:01.460 --> 32:02.959
Remember me?

32:02.960 --> 32:04.459
Smitty's rookie?

32:04.460 --> 32:06.119
Had you dead to rights
on a parole violation?

32:06.120 --> 32:08.039
Yeah.
What do you want?

32:08.040 --> 32:10.419
Your boy.
Gleason Dunn.

32:10.420 --> 32:11.499
Tell me where he is,

32:11.500 --> 32:13.169
and these officers
might just let you go.

32:13.170 --> 32:14.249
He's not my boy.

32:14.250 --> 32:16.039
He destroyed a family today,

32:16.040 --> 32:17.539
dumped a gun
for a child to find.

32:17.540 --> 32:18.879
Life's full of tragedy.

32:18.880 --> 32:21.879
You want your life
to become one?

32:21.880 --> 32:23.879
'Cause I'm hoping for a couple
more decades on the job,

32:23.880 --> 32:25.919
years I will spend
making your life a living hell

32:25.920 --> 32:27.329
if you don't come clean.

32:27.330 --> 32:29.579
Is that really something
you want to sign up for?

32:29.580 --> 32:31.789
'Cause it seems smarter to just
give the guy up and go home.

32:31.790 --> 32:37.669
♪♪

32:37.670 --> 32:39.419
Police!

32:39.420 --> 32:47.420
♪♪

32:50.830 --> 32:55.959
♪♪

32:55.960 --> 33:01.920
♪♪

33:12.710 --> 33:17.959
♪♪

33:17.960 --> 33:23.459
♪♪

33:23.460 --> 33:28.709
♪♪

33:28.710 --> 33:34.920
♪♪

33:37.290 --> 33:40.619
♪♪

33:40.620 --> 33:44.710
♪♪

33:52.620 --> 33:58.499
♪♪

33:58.500 --> 34:05.670
♪♪

34:08.880 --> 34:16.539
♪♪

34:16.540 --> 34:21.329
♪♪

34:21.330 --> 34:24.960
♪♪

34:29.620 --> 34:32.079
Passwords,
or I start taking off ears.

34:32.080 --> 34:33.498
I don't... I don't...

34:33.500 --> 34:35.418
I don't know them
off the top of my head, man.

34:35.420 --> 34:36.829
I got them stored
back at my place!

34:36.830 --> 34:38.289
Nice try.

34:38.290 --> 34:40.289
Guess I'm taking some pieces off
to get the truth.

34:40.290 --> 34:42.208
I'm telling you the truth!
I swear! Come on!

34:42.210 --> 34:44.248
Police!
Drop the saw!

34:44.250 --> 34:46.958
Stand up right now,
or I will shoot you.

34:46.960 --> 34:48.000
Do not test me.

34:49.580 --> 34:54.579
♪♪

34:54.580 --> 34:56.918
Okay.
Okay, you got me.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.249
Back up. Hands behind your head.
Interlace your fingers.

34:59.250 --> 35:01.669
No problem, officer,
but I got a bad shoulder.

35:01.670 --> 35:04.000
Shut up.
Turn around.

35:05.540 --> 35:07.919
I don't know if I can...

35:07.920 --> 35:09.540
Stay right there.

35:11.290 --> 35:12.920
♪♪

35:15.880 --> 35:16.919
You see where he went?

35:16.920 --> 35:18.169
No, I didn't see where he went.

35:18.170 --> 35:20.000
Can you get this damn saw
away from me?

35:23.040 --> 35:24.499
Can you walk?
I don't think so.

35:24.500 --> 35:26.329
Stay right there.
I don't think
I have a choice.

35:26.330 --> 35:27.579
Give me your backup.

35:27.580 --> 35:29.250
Come on, man.
I need a weapon.

35:30.750 --> 35:32.209
Got it?

35:32.210 --> 35:37.829
♪♪

35:37.830 --> 35:43.669
♪♪

35:43.670 --> 35:50.710
♪♪

36:03.540 --> 36:05.120
You're under arrest.

36:06.880 --> 36:12.919
♪♪

36:12.920 --> 36:18.829
♪♪

36:18.830 --> 36:22.039
♪ Well, I ain't no old dog ♪

36:22.040 --> 36:25.419
♪ But I got
a trick or two, baby ♪

36:25.420 --> 36:28.999
♪ It ain't what I wanted ♪

36:29.000 --> 36:32.379
♪ But I gotta
give it to ya, baby ♪

36:32.380 --> 36:34.620
♪ You been on my mind ♪

36:36.420 --> 36:38.919
Well done, Officer West.

36:38.920 --> 36:42.329
♪ You don't need no textbook ♪

36:42.330 --> 36:45.749
♪ Baby, I can teach it to you
right now ♪

36:45.750 --> 36:47.790
♪ If you're willing to try ♪

36:49.380 --> 36:50.789
Hi.

36:50.790 --> 36:52.209
I'm sorry.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.379
Just, every time
I go to my mother's house,

36:54.380 --> 36:56.119
I turn into this person
I don't want to be.

36:56.120 --> 36:58.039
Why?
Your mom is great.

36:58.040 --> 37:00.249
And don't give me the "You don't
really know her" spiel.

37:00.250 --> 37:02.669
She has nothing but a deep
and genuine love for you.

37:02.670 --> 37:04.459
So why do you keep
turning your back on her?

37:04.460 --> 37:07.579
It's just all that excess.
I always hated that.

37:07.580 --> 37:09.579
I need to make it on my own.

37:09.580 --> 37:11.289
What?

37:11.290 --> 37:13.249
Only a rich person would think

37:13.250 --> 37:15.080
turning down money
is a noble idea.

37:16.710 --> 37:19.039
I wore my brother's
hand-me-downs until I was 15.

37:19.040 --> 37:20.169
My mom worked two jobs,

37:20.170 --> 37:22.419
and so did we
once we reached high school.

37:22.420 --> 37:24.579
So...
you think less of me?

37:24.580 --> 37:25.999
Are you kidding?

37:26.000 --> 37:28.040
Your mom and I already started
planning the wedding.

37:29.120 --> 37:30.579
California's
a no-fault divorce state,

37:30.580 --> 37:32.119
so if you ever felt like
doing me a solid...

37:32.120 --> 37:33.539
Mm-hmm.

37:33.540 --> 37:36.919
♪♪

37:36.920 --> 37:39.579
Love your mom
while you have her.

37:39.580 --> 37:41.829
Take that money
and do something good with it.

37:41.830 --> 37:43.209
Like fix your car, maybe?

37:43.210 --> 37:45.329
I was thinking more like
feed the homeless,

37:45.330 --> 37:47.209
but I wouldn't say no
to a Porsche.

37:47.210 --> 37:48.579
Oh, really?

37:48.580 --> 37:51.119
Or we could just get
a chauffeur.

37:51.120 --> 37:52.500
Come on, trust fund.

37:53.750 --> 37:56.579
♪♪

37:56.580 --> 37:58.499
♪ Baby, it's just
too hard to tell ♪

37:58.500 --> 37:59.579
Mm!

37:59.580 --> 38:01.829
♪♪

38:01.830 --> 38:03.959
Two hours
till we're back on shift.

38:03.960 --> 38:05.289
It's gonna be a long day.

38:05.290 --> 38:06.709
Think you can get
a power nap in?

38:06.710 --> 38:07.959
Nah.

38:07.960 --> 38:09.830
I'm just gonna
"Clockwork Orange" it.

38:12.120 --> 38:14.459
Hey, come on.
Gleason's behind bars.

38:14.460 --> 38:15.879
You gotta feel good
about that, right?

38:15.880 --> 38:17.380
Yeah.

38:18.750 --> 38:21.579
But if I wouldn't have pushed
things with my problem spot,

38:21.580 --> 38:25.209
if I would have just sat
in the car, like Smitty said,

38:25.210 --> 38:27.879
or... or let the ex-cons go
with a warning,

38:27.880 --> 38:29.829
then Gleason wouldn't have run
and he wouldn't have...

38:29.830 --> 38:31.329
He wouldn't have dumped
the gun, and that kid
would still have a mom.

38:31.330 --> 38:33.289
Stop.

38:33.290 --> 38:35.829
What happened
was not your fault.

38:35.830 --> 38:38.579
It was Gleason's, and now he's
on the hook for two murders.

38:38.580 --> 38:40.499
He's gonna be locked up forever.

38:40.500 --> 38:42.419
That's all you need
to take away from this.

38:42.420 --> 38:43.829
You got me?

38:43.830 --> 38:45.079
Yeah.

38:45.080 --> 38:46.619
And don't start listening
to Smitty.

38:46.620 --> 38:48.379
You're not that kind of cop.

38:48.380 --> 38:50.459
Yeah, I'm the kind who'll never
get out of long sleeves.

38:50.460 --> 38:52.669
Mm!
Excuse me?

38:52.670 --> 38:55.119
Sorry. Your bet.
Clearly, you won't, either.

38:55.120 --> 38:56.669
Do you really think
Tim's gonna make me do push-ups

38:56.670 --> 38:57.670
after every call?

38:58.920 --> 39:00.379
You know what?
On the bright side,

39:00.380 --> 39:02.710
when it's over, I'm gonna have
mad upper-body strength.

39:04.210 --> 39:05.999
Come on.
I'll drop you off at your car.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.169
We still got time to shower
and change before roll call.

39:08.170 --> 39:09.750
Let's go.

39:11.580 --> 39:13.079
How's Mejia?

39:13.080 --> 39:14.789
They took him back into surgery,

39:14.790 --> 39:17.079
but, um, I think
he's gonna be okay.

39:17.080 --> 39:18.289
And did you get a chance
to talk to him?

39:18.290 --> 39:19.829
I got the passwords,

39:19.830 --> 39:22.919
and we seized $22 million
in assets from the arms dealer.

39:22.920 --> 39:25.249
And you helped take down
a pretty big operation, John.

39:25.250 --> 39:26.919
Despite the fact
I almost screwed it up.

39:26.920 --> 39:30.079
Well, everyone makes a mistake
now and then.

39:30.080 --> 39:31.919
Like the one
I made yesterday with you?

39:31.920 --> 39:34.209
Look, um...

39:34.210 --> 39:37.039
I-I wasn't asking
to live with you.

39:37.040 --> 39:39.289
I was, uh...

39:39.290 --> 39:40.789
I was just testing the waters.

39:40.790 --> 39:42.539
And I capsized the boat.

39:42.540 --> 39:45.539
Look, Jess...

39:45.540 --> 39:49.619
I am still just figuring out
who I am in this new life.

39:49.620 --> 39:52.419
It hasn't even been a year
since I got divorced,

39:52.420 --> 39:56.829
and I got a brand-new job,
entirely new city.

39:56.830 --> 40:00.749
The only thing
I know for sure is...

40:00.750 --> 40:02.499
I love spending time with you.

40:02.500 --> 40:06.499
And a shoe rack
will add value to my home,

40:06.500 --> 40:07.919
and if you have
any more great ideas...

40:07.920 --> 40:09.289
I'd love to hear them.

40:09.290 --> 40:11.079
♪♪

40:11.080 --> 40:12.419
Deal.

40:12.420 --> 40:15.749
♪♪

40:15.750 --> 40:17.250
I gotta go.

40:21.460 --> 40:24.579
Look at you, saving the world,
getting the girl.

40:24.580 --> 40:26.329
Far cry from college,
when all you wanted

40:26.330 --> 40:28.329
was a fake ID
and to pass organic chem.

40:28.330 --> 40:29.790
Well, it wasn't all I wanted.

40:31.750 --> 40:34.289
You had your charms.

40:34.290 --> 40:37.329
Hey, um, I wanted to apologize

40:37.330 --> 40:39.499
about that crack
about Agent Russo

40:39.500 --> 40:42.079
and for assuming
that I know your taste.

40:42.080 --> 40:44.169
I mean, 20 years is a long time.

40:44.170 --> 40:46.579
And yet you are
exactly how I remember you.

40:46.580 --> 40:49.329
I'm not sure if that's
a positive or a negative.

40:49.330 --> 40:50.790
Positive, for sure.
And this has...

40:52.580 --> 40:54.709
This has been great
seeing you again

40:54.710 --> 40:57.039
and catching up
and being friends again.

40:57.040 --> 40:58.419
Mm-hmm.
And I would love to go

40:58.420 --> 40:59.820
on a double date,
meet your husband.

41:00.960 --> 41:02.579
I'm not really married.

41:02.580 --> 41:03.999
Oh, I-I...

41:04.000 --> 41:05.619
I mean, technically, I am,

41:05.620 --> 41:08.209
but Simon and I...
We separated over a year ago.

41:08.210 --> 41:09.249
I'm sorry.

41:09.250 --> 41:11.079
Yeah, I guess
that I keep wearing the ring

41:11.080 --> 41:12.999
so I don't have to have
uncomfortable conversations.

41:13.000 --> 41:14.919
Right. I get it.
Um...

41:14.920 --> 41:16.459
And I know the drill.

41:16.460 --> 41:19.210
So if you ever want
to just talk, I'm... I'm around.

41:20.960 --> 41:23.169
I might just
take you up on that.

41:23.170 --> 41:27.580
♪♪

41:31.210 --> 41:33.329
Lucy!
What are you doing here?

41:33.330 --> 41:34.919
Uh, sorry.
I know it's early.

41:34.920 --> 41:36.829
Um, I just wanted to thank you

41:36.830 --> 41:39.419
for going out with Tim
last night.

41:39.420 --> 41:42.209
Uh, Bordeaux,
your favorite wine, right?

41:42.210 --> 41:44.040
That wasn't necessary.

41:47.080 --> 41:48.879
I hope it wasn't too unbearable.

41:48.880 --> 41:51.289
It was fine.
He was... fine.

41:51.290 --> 41:54.209
I know he can come off
like this smug hard-ass,

41:54.210 --> 41:56.830
but, you know, deep down, he...
He has a really good heart.

41:57.880 --> 41:59.579
Anyway, I'll go.

41:59.580 --> 42:01.500
But I owe you one.
Big time.

42:02.880 --> 42:06.329
♪♪

42:06.330 --> 42:07.959
Hey, can I borrow your, uh...

42:07.960 --> 42:11.580
♪♪

42:13.210 --> 42:15.249
Short sleeves.

42:15.250 --> 42:21.329
♪♪

42:21.330 --> 42:22.330
Yes!

42:26.580 --> 42:34.580
♪♪

42:34.620 --> 42:42.329
♪♪

42:42.330 --> 42:50.169
♪♪

42:50.170 --> 42:58.000
♪♪

42:59.040 --> 43:00.040
Damn it!

43:00.041 --> 43:01.710
♪♪
